---
import ContentLayout from "@layouts/ContentLayout.astro";
import Feature from "@components/Feature.astro";
---

<ContentLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Cayce House — a Systems Administrator in Greenville, NC focused on Linux infrastructure, automation, and security."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <div class="mb-2"><Feature /></div>
    <h1 class="text-center text-4xl font-light md:text-5xl">About me</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert mx-auto mt-8 max-w-none prose-a:text-indigo-400">
      <p>
        I'm Cayce House, a Systems Administrator based in Greenville, North
        Carolina. I spend my days keeping Linux infrastructure reliable, secure,
        and automated — and a good chunk of my evenings doing the same thing for
        fun in a homelab.
      </p>
      <p>
        I work on the ITCS Linux Team at East Carolina University, where I
        automate provisioning and configuration management for RHEL and Debian
        servers with Ansible and Puppet, run critical university services, and
        act as an escalation point when things break. Along the way I've
        architected an OKD (OpenShift) single-node platform for departmental
        testing and wired up self-hosted CI/CD runners to speed up internal
        development.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before the Linux team I supported large Apple and clinical-device fleets
        at ECU's School of Dental Medicine and ran lab infrastructure across
        campus — deploying thousands of devices, building monitoring and
        ticketing tooling, and mentoring student technicians. That mix of
        hands-on support and infrastructure work is where I learned to keep
        systems stable while still moving fast.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm currently pursuing a Master of Science in Information and
        Cybersecurity Technology, with a focus on enterprise security
        architecture and IT compliance. Outside of work I run a multi-node
        Kubernetes cluster using GitOps workflows, build CI/CD pipelines with
        GitHub Actions, and lean on Prometheus and Grafana to actually
        understand what my systems are doing.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is where I document that work. Have a look at my
        <a href="/projects">projects</a>, read the <a href="/blog">blog</a>, or
        skim my <a href="/resume">resume</a>. If you'd like to get in touch,
        <a href="mailto:cayce@caycehouse.com">email me</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</ContentLayout>
